        "type": "text",
        "text": "The equation of the curve is in reality\n\n$y^2 = 4ax$ \n\nby setting in place of $L$ and in place of $D.$"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Thus\n\n$$\n\\frac{dy}{dx} = \\frac{4a}{4a} = 1,\n$$"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "so that\n\n$$\n\\sqrt{1 + \\left( \\frac{dy}{dx} \\right)^2} = \\sqrt{1 + (1)^2} = \\sqrt{2}.\n$$"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "or\n\nwhen\n\n$$\n\\sqrt{1 + \\left( \\frac{dy}{dx} \\right)^2} = \\sqrt{1 + (1)^2}.\n$$"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Thus\n\n$$\nL = \\int_{}^{} \\sqrt{1 + \\left( \\frac{dy}{dx} \\right)^2} \\, dy = \\int_{}^{} \\sqrt{2} \\, dy.\n$$"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Hence\n\n$$\ns = 2 \\int_0^{} \\sqrt{2} \\, dy = 2 \\sqrt{2} y + C,\n$$"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "where $C$ is constant."
      },
